-- Lithuanian Wages Grew 2.8% in Fourth Quarter Driven by Bonuses
-- B y   M i l d a   S e p u t y t e
-- 2012-02-23T10:19:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/lithuanian-wages-grew-2-8-in-fourth-quarter-driven-by-bonuses.html
Lithuanian wages grew 2.8 percent
from the previous quarter in the October-December period, driven
by bonuses and other one-time payments.  The average monthly gross wage increased to 2,175 litai
($839), the statistics office in the capital, Vilnius, said
today in an e-mailed statement. Wages rose 2.5 percent from the
same period of 2010.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Milda Seputyte in Vilnius at 
